name: Florida communism bill
summary: Florida Governor Ron DeSantis has signed a bill into law that mandates the teaching of anti-communist principles in public schools from kindergarten to grade 12. The legislation requires schools to educate students about the "evils of communism" and its historical impact on the United States and other societies. The move has been met with mixed reactions, with some praising the emphasis on countering communist ideology while others express concerns about potential bias or political indoctrination in classrooms. The law aims to promote a comprehensive understanding of communism's negative consequences and its threat to democratic values.

summary: Multiple states experienced 911 outages due to an issue with Lumen, a 911 service provider. summary: Quentin Tarantino has reportedly abandoned plans to make "The Movie Critic" as his final film. The news comes after the director previously announced that his tenth film would be his last. Tarantino's "The Movie Critic" was set to focus on a fictional character named Leo Kessler, a renowned film critic living in the 1970s. The film was expected to explore themes of criticism, nostalgia, and the changing landscape of Hollywood.

name: Kerry Kennedy
summary: The Kennedy family has overwhelmingly endorsed Joe Biden for president, distancing themselves from their family member Robert F. Kennedy Jr., who is running as an independent candidate against Biden. The family endorsement is seen as an attempt to rally support for Biden and counter the growing momentum behind RFK Jr.'s campaign. Kennedy family members have expressed strong support for Biden, with Kerry Kennedy stating that "this is the most important election of my lifetime" and Kathleen Kennedy Townsend emphasizing that the endorsement makes "crystal clear" the family's preference for Biden. The Kennedy endorsement adds to the growing list of high-profile endorsements for Biden, who has also received support from former President Barack Obama and former Secretary of State Hillary Clinton.

name: No Rest for the Wicked
summary: No Rest For The Wicked, the upcoming action-platformer from Moon Studios, has released a launch trailer promising no microtransactions, always-online features, or anti-cheat. The game enters Early Access this week, costing $39.99, with plans for a full release later. No Rest For The Wicked will be available on PC and Xbox, and will also be playable on Steam Deck. The game showcases significant graphics advancements compared to Moon Studios' previous title, Ori and the Blind Forest. Despite meeting the Steam Deck's recommended specifications, No Rest For The Wicked may still face performance issues on the handheld console.
